# ── Database ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Postgres connection string.
#  • Set it  → the app uses it (Neon in production, or any Postgres locally).
#  • Empty   → the app falls back to an embedded Postgres (PGlite) stored in
#              ./.pglite, auto-migrated and seeded. Zero setup for local dev.
#
# Create a free database at https://neon.tech, then paste its *pooled*
# connection string here (and into Vercel's Environment Variables for prod):
DATABASE_URL=

# ── Display (optional) ───────────────────────────────────
# Currency symbol + locale used when formatting amounts.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CURRENCY=₹
NEXT_PUBLIC_LOCALE=en-IN
